@startuml seq_14_reply_to_comment
title Sequence Diagram: UC-14 Reply to Comment

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Comment Controller" as Controller
participant "Comment Service" as Service
participant "Comment Repo" as CommentRepo
participant "Post Repo" as PostRepo
participant "Event Bus\n(Go Channels)" as EventBus

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open a comment thread
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Write a reply
User -> Frontend: (3.1) Submit the reply
Frontend -> Controller: (3.2) POST /api/comments/{parent_id}/reply {content}
Controller -> Service: (4.1) Create reply request
Service -> CommentRepo: (4.2) Validate authentication and parent comment
CommentRepo --> Service: (4.3) Parent is valid (postID)

Service -> CommentRepo: (5.1) Create reply with parent_id
CommentRepo --> Service: (5.2) Reply created
Service -> PostRepo: (6.1) Increment post comment count
PostRepo --> Service: (6.2) Count updated

Service -> EventBus: (6.3) Publish ReplyCreatedEvent
note right of EventBus
  Background goroutine notifies
  the parent comment author
end note

Service --> Controller: (7.1) Created reply data
Controller --> Frontend: (7.2) 201 Created
Frontend --> User: (7.3) Render reply under parent
@enduml
